# Intuition
Check Every Row,Column,Box, if there is duplicate of not.
We will do it in one iteration.

# Approach
There will be 9 row, 9 col and 9 box. We can determine the row and col no. easily (i,j if we iterate throw board ). And to to determine the box no --> [(i/3)*3 +(j/3)] ;

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(N*N)

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    bool isValidSudoku(vector<vector<char>>& board) {
        set<char> row[9];
        set<char> col[9];
        set<char> box[9];
        for(int i=0;i<9;i++)
        {
            for(int j=0;j<9;j++)
            {
                char ch=board[i][j];
                if(ch=='.') continue;

                <!-- Checking the Row -->
                if(row[i].count(ch)>=1) return false;
                else row[i].insert(ch);

