# Approach
The question is asking us to check whether any integer between 1-9 appears more than once in a particular row, column, or 3x3 grid.

For this, we will create three hash arrays, a, b, and c. Array a will check whether any integer from 1 to 9 appears more than once in a particular row, array b will check whether any integer from 1 to 9 appears more than once in a particular column, and array c will check whether any integer from 1 to 9 appears more than once in a particular 3x3 grid.

If any of these conditions are true, we will return false; otherwise, we will return true

