Here is my approach for the problem
the intuation and approach explained:
to make the string palindrome we may add substring from the start to position i reversed at the end or add substring from end to position j at the start
so i have 2 map saving the string reversed and normal
if we have a closer look, when we add x elements at the end the we sure that the first x element match with the last x element since the substring that we will add will be the first x elements reversed , so we check from postion x + 1 to size - 1 to see if the string will be palindrome
the same idea works when we add substring to the start we only need to check from index 0 to index x - 1 and see if its palindrome.
when it is a palindrome i add the pair into a set to avoid any repetaing pairs 
another point is we have to use unordered map not a normal map to do the operation in constat time 
the complexity will be O(N * M^2) where M is the max size of the string.
