Explanation : First Insert all strings in reverse order, then search for each string , whether it forms a palindorme or not in Trie.

Note-> If some characters matches while searching, then check if all other substrings after this point, are they palindrome or not.

there are two cases for a palindrome of two strings

case 1:
    let the strings be [bd, dbccc]
    here the words will be inserted in reverse order
	so while searching 
    i=1;
    dbccc
    we find first two characters of dbccc in trie(as bd s inserted in reverse), so other three characters should be palindrome, the other characters should be checked seperately,

case 2:
    let the strings be "abacd", "dc"  
    here the words will be inserted in reverse order
    so while searching
    for i=1
    dc
    we will find dc in the tree(as abacd is inserted in reverse), the remaining 3 elements aba in the trie, should be checked for palindrome
