solutions.content:
There are KMPs, so this is based on Z-algoritm, which is easier to code. If you don't know kmp or Z, learn and write a template for them. Then the thing is easy as this is exatcly problem 214, you extend your string to make a palindorm and search in map. Some tricks will be used like you only extend to twice length -1 and you both extend before and back( do 214 for 2 times). And you extend twice length before for distint result. Those tricks are trivial, once you know Z and 214, this problem is easy. The running time is good as kmp O(nk) roughly, k as length of cur processing string.
```
int match_length(string & s, int pos1, int pos2){

    int length = 0;

    //当前字符match，延长长度
    while (length + pos2 < s.size() && s[length+pos1] == s[length+pos2] ) {
        length++;
    }

    return length;
}

vector<int> z_algorithm(string & s){

    vector<int> z_array(s.size(),0);
    //左右窗口初始化 设为-1 左右inclusive 表示当前最远能match到的地方（r） 和开始match时的位置 lr始终是 从l开始最长的prefix
    int l = -1;
    int r = -1;

    for (int i = 1; i< s.size(); i++) {
        //情况1，当前位置比之前最远match位置远，从当前位置和string开头开始match，updata l，r
        if (i > r) {
            int length = match_length(s,0,i);
            l = i;
            r = i + length - 1;
            z_array[i] = length;
        } else {
            //情况2，当前位置处于之前最远match里面，那么我们可以直接通过查表得知可能的match，和表中确定的match
            int lastMatch = z_array[i-l];

            //2-1  可能的match比已有大或者等于，意味着现在的r有拓展性， 应为l到r是prefix 从k到r一定match，1，有机会拓展
            if (i+lastMatch-1 >= r) {
